g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: if the _smh-acknowledgement-status of any smh-message-server SMH is unacknowledged then start {refresh-filter-name} sc-smh-refresh-status (SMH)
if the _smh-acknowledgement-status of any smh-message-server SMH is acknowledged then start {refresh-filter-name} sc-smh-refresh-status (SMH)
if the _smh-highest-message-priority of any smh-message-server SMH has a current value then start {refresh-filter-name} sc-smh-refresh-status (SMH)
whenever the sc-attribute-name of any sc-attribute-filter SOF receives a value and when the sc-active of SOF then start sc-refresh (SOF)
whenever the sc-attribute-value of any sc-attribute-filter SOF receives a value and when the sc-active of SOF then start sc-refresh (SOF)

g2:c.METHOD.g2:a.TEXT: sc-calculate-filter-data (F: class sc-filter) {Bug fix: HQ-1476044, this method is called in sc-browser-queue::sc-initialize, does nothing} begin end
set-filter-data(F: class sc-schematic-object-filter, Target : class _opfo-domain-object ) begin conclude that the sc-filter-object of F = devu-ext-name-or-name-as-string (Target); end

g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: whenever the sc-filter-object of any sc-schematic-object-filter SOF receives a value and when the sc-active of SOF then start sc-refresh (SOF)
initially for any sc-toggle-button SPF if the sc-active of SPF then change the checked-color icon-color of SPF to black

initially for any sc-priority-filter SPF if (the sc-attribute-value of SPF exists and the sc-attribute-value of SPF is an integer) then start opfom-set-alarm-status (SPF, the sc-attribute-value of SPF)

whenever the sc-attribute-value of any sc-priority-filter SCF receives a value and when (the sc-attribute-value of SCF exists and the sc-attribute-value of SCF is an integer) then start opfom-set-alarm-status (SCF, the sc-attribute-value of SCF)

g2:c.METHOD.g2:a.TEXT: sc-get-filter-classification-key (Filter: class sc-attribute-filter) = (symbol) begin return the sc-attribute-name of Filter; end
sc-get-filter-classification-key (Filter: class sc-filter) = (symbol) begin return the class of Filter; end

g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: whenever the sc-publisher of any sc-smh-subscriber Sub receives a value then start sc-refresh-status-subscription (Sub)
whenever the sc-publisher of any sc-smh-status-subscriber Sub receives a value then start sc-refresh-status-subscription (Sub)

c.OPFO-STRIPPABLE-COMMENT.g2:a.TEXT: 11/5/97 DVG Created an sc-tool-bar-backdrop message object to replace the toolbar object on the browser, see bug HQ-1595592 for additional information.

10/29/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: HQ-1652875. Added two whenever rules so that the browser is refreshed when an attribute-value or the attribute-name specified in a filter receives a new value when the filter is toggled on.

10/29/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: HQ-1652871. Modified the method SC-ATTRIBUTE-FILTER::GQS-APPLY-FILTER so that the filtering criteria fails when the attribute itself does not exists. Also changed to use item-or-value for indirect reference of the value of an attribute by name in g2 5.0r1.

10/20/97 DVG Added the attribute sc-auto-layout to the class sc-status-display. This attribute is used by the scrollui.kb in determing whether an auto layout of the status display is performed, see _scrollui-add-status-bar-to-storage-bin for more information.

07/18/97 Ramesh Defined a new method sc-schematic-object-filter::sc-delete. Since the deletion of sc-schematic-object-filter::sc-toggle (and the comment out the code that was deleting FilterObjList in c-schematic-object-filter::sc-toggle) was causing a memory leak of FilterObjList upon deleting a sc-schematic-object-filter from menu-choice.

07/17/97 Ramesh Modified sc-filter::sc-toggle to add a call to sc-calculate-filter-data when the filter is toggled on. And deleted sc-schematic-object-filter::sc-toggle which was basically calling sc-calculate-filter-data method before a "call next method". Since now there is a sc-filter::sc-calculate-filter-data defined

07/17/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: HQ-1472498 , Modified sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-additive-or-filter-addition to use BrowserQueue (instead of Queue) as the first argument in the call to gqs-send-items. This arg. is the sender and is not used in the called proc. When no subscribers were toggled on the use of Queue was creating a "no item" error.

07/17/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: HQ-1476044, Modified sc-browser-queue::sc-initialize to call sc-calculate-filter-data in order to appropriately initialize the target/sender filters. Also defined sc-filter::sc-calculate-filter-data which does nothing.

07/15/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Modified sc-schematic-object-filter::sc-toggle to comment out the code that was deleting FilterObjList. since FilterObjList is needed later in gqs-apply-filter and when multiple target/sender filters exists, when toggling them off does not remove items appropriately from the browser .

06/04/97 William Modified sc-browser-queue::sc-refresh. An error was being produced when no subscriber was selected and toggling on and off a filter. The error turned out to be QUEUE was referenced when it had no value. QUEUE is used to iterate over the selected servers, but a call outside the for loop was using QUEUE. I created a dummy item and replaced it with QUEUE in the call that was producing the error.
05/13/97 Ramesh Changed the attribute-initializations for sc-browser-queue, to none since all gqs-queue attributes default to false/unspecified, also.

05/13/97 Ramesh Changed the procedures sc-browser-queue::sc-initialize, sc-browser-queue::sc-refresh, sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-additive-or-filter-addition, sc-subscriber::sc-toggle to use the new API gqsv-get-current-sort-key.

05/13/97 Ramesh Replaced the old gqs-clear-buffers with appropriate calls to gqs-force-input-buffer-into-queue or gqs-clear-input-buffer in sc-browser-queue::sc-initialize, sc-browser-queue::sc-refresh, sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-additive-or-filter-addition, sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-restrictive-and-filter-addition, sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-restrictive-or-filter-removal, sc-subscriber::sc-toggle, sc-smh-subscriber::sc-unsubscribe.
05/12/97 Ramesh Added attribute-initializations for sc-browser-queue; Removed sc-widget as the superior class of sc-browser-template
05/12/97 Ramesh Changed sc-smh-subscriber::sc-unsubscribe to use gqs-get-subscriptions-from-queue-to-queue

05/12/97 Ramesh Performance improvement: Changed sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-additive-or-filter-addition so that all items in all subscribed queues are collected first in a for loop and then the gqs operations are perfromed once. Also commented out the "allow other processing".

05/12/97 Ramesh Performance improvement: Changed sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-restrictive-and-filter-addition so that the items that have to be removed are decided by list subtaction and removed from BrowserQueue.

05/12/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Changed SC-UPDATE-FOR-RESTRICTIVE-OR-FILTER-REMOVAL so that the items that have to be removed are decided by list subtaction (since OR filters can have overlap e.g., wildcard filters).

05/09/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Changed the methods sc-smh-status-subscriber::sc-refresh-status and sc-smh-subscriber::sc-refresh-status so that when the servers ack-status is not acknowledged the ack-color-region is changed to black/transparent. HQ-1338932.

05/05/97 Ramesh In order to use the new buffered GQS, has to include calls to call gqsv-force-all-scheduled-updates before forcing sorting in the browser, in sc-browser-queue::sc-refresh, sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-restrictive-and-filter-addition (using gqs-clear-queue followed by gqs-send-items, gqs-clear-buffers, gqsv-sort in these methods). Otherwise get white lines and sort error later ("The result of the ROUND expression, -Inf, is out of the range of integers. Operation: round(-Inf) Activity: assign local variable statement Within: _GQSV-SORT-DESCENDING" ).

05/05/97 Ramesh Forcing default time-order sorting in the browser, unless a column header is selected for sorting (since by default adding new items at the end of the scroll when automatically-sort-new-item is false) in sc-subscriber::sc-toggle, sc-browser-queue::sc-refresh, sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-additive-or-filter-addition, sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-restrictive-and-filter-addition, sc-browser-queue::sc-initialize

05/05/97 Ramesh In order to use the new buffered GQS, has to include calls to gqs-clear-buffers in sc-subscriber::sc-toggle, sc-smh-subscriber::sc-unsubscribe, sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-restrictive-or-filter-removal, sc-browser-queue::sc-refresh, sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-additive-or-filter-addition, sc-browser-queue::sc-update-for-restrictive-and-filter-addition, sc-browser-queue::sc-initialize
05/01/97 Ramesh Changed sc-delete-browser-queue to use API in GQSV instead of using GXL API.

04/30/97 Ramesh Removed the Browser-workspace as argument for sc-browser-queue::sc-refresh and also removed the locking and unlocking of the browser-view at the begining and the end of this method (only for which the browser-wksp was required) and in sc-browser-queue::sc-initialize, sc-subscriber::sc-toggle (not necessary).

04/30/97 Ramesh Performance improvement in Filtering: Changed sc-browser-queue::sc-add-filter and sc-browser-queue::sc-remove-filter so that it returns a truth-value indicating whether the filter is additive or restrictive. Also changed sc-filter::sc-toggle so that it does efficient BrowserQueue/view updates for toggling-on/off filters using the newly defined methods sc-update-for-additive-or-filter-addition, sc-update-for-restrictive-and-filter-addition, sc-update-for-restrictive-or-filter-removal .

04/28/97 Ramesh Performance improvement by changing sc-smh-subscriber::sc-unsubscribe not to iterate over all items in Publisher. Instead used gqs-remove-items (BrowserQueue, PubItems, Win) . if the assumption that an item will not be in two queues, which is true for smh-transient-messages and servers, and also not allowing two subscribers to the same server on the browser, which is generally true, this improves performance atleast twice .
04/9/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Removed the menu choices clone and transfer in developer mode in the class definition sc-toggle-button.

04/9/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Defined new methods sc-smh-status-subscriber::sc-refresh-status-subscription and sc-smh-subscriber::sc-refresh-status-subscription and whenever rules which starts these methods when the sc-publisher gets a new value.
04/8/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Changed the menu-option of sc-toggle-button, sc-subscriber, sc-filter, sc-schematic-object-filter to "not a final menu-choice".

04/8/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Changed the Subscriber argument type of the methods sc-browser-queue::sc-add-subscriber and sc-browser-queue::sc-remove-subscriber to sc-subscriber (was sc-smh-subscriber earlier).

04/8/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Changed the Subscriber argument type of the methods sc-browser-queue::sc-add-subscriber and sc-browser-queue::sc-remove-subscriber to sc-subscriber (was sc-smh-subscriber earlier).
04/8/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Provided new API method sc-delete for sc-toggle-button for deleting subscribers and filters on browsers.
03/20/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: In procedure sc-schematic-object-filter::sc-calculate-filter-data found all the subworkspce children for opfo-managed as well as opfo-containment objects.
03/20/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: In procedure sc-delete-browser-queue added "make wksp transient" before deleting it, since uil makes the wksp permenanat.

03/13/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Changed the procedures sc-display-browser and sc-display-status so that these procedures check for "not (there exists an item that is the-sc-smh-status-publisher-of Subscriber)" before trying to find a publisher to set the relation. This change is needed due to the change in twn-display-screen where by the twm-display-procedure is now executed each time the browser/status workspaces are shown.
03/06/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Changed sc-attribute-filter::gqs-apply-filter so that it checks for the existance of the sc-attribute-value of AF.
03/06/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Changed sc-priority-filter::opfom-set-alarm-status so that it sets the check-box icon-color appropriately.
03/04/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Changed sc-browser-queue::sc-remove-subscriber so that it checks for the existance of a Publisher before trying to unsubscribe a subscriber.
1/28/97 Ramesh Major Changes MAK's gqs and gqsview modules are now used for Fault Expert's browser. All the unused old browser stuff is in sc-browser-unused.

11/27/96 Ramesh Changed the method sc-delete-views so that when a sc-dynamic-refresh button upon the browser is not selected then no refresh on deletion of messages or items. (will just leave a hole in place).
11/22/96 Ramesh Changed the method sc-check-filter-criteria so that it accounts for the sc-dynamic-refresh button upon the browser (if any).
11/21/96 Ramesh Renamed CMH's sc-clone method on the sc-browser as devu-clone. The method devu-clone is needed for cloning a sc-browser since, CMH uses uil stuff on browser!

11/21/96 Christine Moved UI back in, fixed scroll bar method to change colors correctly as user scrolls, fixed sc-refresh-frame to handle messages that are longer than the frame itself, and changed the delete@ user-menu-choice to prompt user before deleting a message (depending on master switch sc-prompt-for-confirmation-during-message-deletion which can be set by the user via an initialization)
11/4/96 Ramesh Moved CHs stuff in message-browser, status-bar from scroll into cmh.
10/31/96 Ramesh Moved the unused scroll items in sc-not-used-anymore in to new opex_unused module.
10/11/96 Ramesh CH's GUI stuff is moved in to OPEX!

10/02/96 Ramesh The new browser is installed and working. The methods and classes are in sc-new-browser-design. This design is based on a publish-subscribe mechanism. Have to use Christine's new "browser icon" instead of subclassing sc-browser from opxb-gr-go-to-subws-button for the icon.
9/17/96 Ramesh Renamed the old sc-frame class to sc-frame-old and changed to this class name in some of its methods also. (for testing the new browser).
9/13/96 Ramesh Other procedures which migh be removed later after the new browser is implemented: SMH-USER-MSG-CREATION-EFFECTS, get-smh-messages, GET-ALL-ANNUNCIATED
9/13/96 Ramesh The method sc-create-subscribed-item-view replaces smh-msg-representation (to be deleted).

9/11/96 Ramesh Deleted the procedure refresh-smh-annunciator. Since sc-smh-annunciator is a subclass of sc-smh-filter, the refresh-filter-name will take care of this. Also made sc-annunciator-name the subclass of sc-filter-name and deleted the relation a-sc-annunciator-name-for which was in between sc-smh-annunciator and sc-annunciator-name. Instead of this now the a-sc-filter-name-for relation will be used. Note: This relation change is made in the procedure initialize-desktop-win in tc_core.
9/6/96 Ramesh Removed the attribute scroll-name from sc-widget, user-data from sc-frame.
8/23/96 Ramesh Added BWAs sc-smh-message-viewer-menu view-details to sc-line.

8/9/96 Ramesh Modified the procedures refresh-smh-annunciator and refresh-filter-name so that these procedures make use of the smh-single-message-list-for-all-telewindows attribute of the simple-message-handler in order to update the colors.

7/29/96 DVG Commented out for loop that referenced EVENTS-WIN, EVENTS-WIN does not exist, in SMH-USER-MSG-CREATION-EFFECTS-OLD procedure, looks as if this procedure is not used any more. DELETE IT ???
7/22/96 Ramesh Modified the alarm-filter function so that it uses smh-standard-background-colors (instead of a non-existing USER-BACKGROUND-COLOR-SET which was used before).

7/18/96 Ramesh Defined a new procedure sc-delete-sc-lines-of-frame-on-wksp in the module scroll for deleting the sc-lines in the item-list displayed in the sc-frame of the browsers before deleting the browsers. This procedure is called from twm-delete-window-mirror and the procedures cdg-delete-dynamic-scroll and delete-fault-isolator.

7/18/96 Ramesh Moved the opxb-gr-go-to-subws-button named table-code from tc_core in to scroll. The subworkspace of this button has the class definitions table-line and table-header; and procedures show-table, hide-table, get-message-class; a relation tb-displayed-by; two mouse-up UMC; an item list table-def-name-list

7/18/96 Ramesh Moved the opxb-gr-go-to-subws-button named scrolling-proc from tc_core in to scroll. The subworkspace of this button has the procedures refresh-smh-annunciator, instance-representation, smh-user-msg-modification-effects, refresh-filter-name, event-filter, generic-iteration-over-smh, smh-user-msg-deletion-effects, smh-msg-representation, smh-user-msg-creation-effects; and three rules which call the refresh-filter-name and refresh-smh-annunciator; and the functions alarm-filter, alphabetical-name, msg-priority, and rank-text.
07/18/96 Ramesh Remodularization: made scroll require smh and removed tw_mgr from the required module for scroll.

07/16/96 Ramesh Modified the procedure sc-filter-button::sc-toggle-filter so that " if Self is a sc-schematic-obj-filter and the filter-data of Self does not exists then return", and "if Self is a sc-schematic-obj-filter and ("[the filter-data of Self]" = "" or "[the filter-data of Self]" = "none" or "[the filter-data of Self]" = "true" or "[the filter-data of Self]" = "false") then return;"

07/16/96 Ramesh Removed the rule "whenever the filter-data of any sc-schematic-obj-filter F receives a value and when sc-checked (F) and the scroll-name of any sc-frame SF upon the workspace of F = the scroll-name of SF then start sc-initialize-scroll (SF) " since there was another same whenever rule for the superior class sc-filter-button .{Brent}

07/16/96 Ramesh Modified the procedures sc-frame::get-smh-messages and sc-schematic-obj-filter::sc-check-filter-criteria so that these procedures use "[the filter-data of the schematic-obj-filter]" instead of assuming that the filter-data will be a text always. Thus the operator can input a symbol also. {Brent}

07/15/96 Ramesh Removed the initialize user-menu-choice for sc-frame which was starting sc-initialize-scroll. Also changed the configuration of the user interface in the class definition of sc-frame that "unless in administrator mode selecting any sc-frame implies initialize", to "selecting any sc-frame does nothing" in order to avoid unnecessary re-initialization of the sc-frame everytime the operator clicks on it.

07/15/96 Ramesh Changed the method sc-button::sc-scroll to make it more efficient: by cheking if the max-index of an sc-frame is > 1 and not (Self is a sc-scroll-bar or ((Self is a sc-top-button or Self is a sc-page-up-button or Self is a sc-up-button) and the message-index of SA = 1) or ((Self is a sc-bottom-button or Self is a sc-page-down-button or Self is a sc-down-button) and the message-index of SA = the max-index of SA)).

07/12/96 Ramesh Changed the methods sc-frame::sc-insert and sc-frame::sc-remove to make them more efficient and return refresh (instead of true allways thus refreshing the scroll in the browser always. Also the relation a-status-diaplay-of which was used in sc-insert does not exist in OPA). The old methods are saved as procedures with -old extension.
06/05/96 BWA Mod. Init rule to look at smh-standard-background-colors instead of user-selected-background-colors
04/18/96 Sknotts Made the revision history workspace private
11/22/95 Sknotts Replaced old module with modified one: procedures converted to methods; workspaces organized; message browser includes an object filter
